pageTitle: Columbine runs out of time in 2nd round | ColumbineCourier.com
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {19881=By Will Petersen For the Courier When you’re losing late, the game clock is a bigger enemy than a Monday morning alarm clock.   Columbine’s boys basketball team saw its season come to an end as a furious fourth-quarter rally came up short in a 61-47 loss to Arapahoe on March 2 in the second round of the 5A state tournament at Columbine High School. Arapahoe (18-7) advances to the Sweet 16 where it will face Fossil Ridge on March 6. “We needed one more quarter. We could’ve had it,” Columbine senior Ty McMinimee said., 32153=Copyright © 2015, 25685=Columbine Courier | circulation@columbinecourier.com | 303-350-1030 5808 S Rapp St, Suite 119, Littleton, CO 80120 Office Hours are 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m., Monday through Friday}
